<item>
            <title>[LU-19344] Performance regression due to file_read_confine_iter added</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19344</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Added by (&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16025&quot; title=&quot;Read past file size after truncate from another client&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-16025&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-16025&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; llite: adjust read count as file got truncated&quot;) to handle read/truncate race.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The cl_io_init / cl_object_attr_get / cl_io_fini cost is excessive when reading from system cache.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;4K reads are ~20% slower on fast_read() and ~5% on BIO&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Maybe we can update attr only when truncate has been issued?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
